    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/north-carolina-supreme-court-republican-judges-violations">
                                    North Carolina Supreme Court Secretly Squashed Discipline of Two GOP Judges Who Admitted to Violating Judicial Code
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            The decisions came despite the Judicial Standards Commission’s recommendations to publicly reprimand the judges, and these are likely the only times in more than a decade in which the court didn’t follow the commission’s guidance.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/doug-bock-clark">Doug Bock Clark</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-06-17EDT05:00">June 17, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

            </div>
</div>
                    


        
                    
<div class="story-card story-card--standard">
    
    

                    
                    
    
        <div class="lead-art">
            <a class="aspect-3-2" href="https://www.propublica.org/article/supreme-connections-database-updated-scotus-disclosures">
                <img
