            </a>
        </div>
    
    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/data-centers-clean-energy-washington-state">
                                    Washington Is Giving Tax Breaks to Data Centers That Threaten the State’s Green Energy Push
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            In 2019, Washington adopted legislation requiring electric utilities to go carbon-neutral in a decade. Yet lawmakers continued to promote the growth of energy-guzzling data centers with generous tax incentives.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <span class="name">Lulu Ramadan</span> and <span class="name">Sydney Brownstone</span>, <a href="http://www.seattletimes.com/">The Seattle Times</a>, photography by <span class="name">Karen Ducey</span>, <a href="http://www.seattletimes.com/">The Seattle Times</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-07-28EDT05:00">July 28, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

                <p class="story-card__unit">Local Reporting Network</p>
            </div>
